# Appwrite + Scriptony (Merksatz)

**Scope:** Cloud browser client, self-hosted, Function deploy, collection deploy, hybrid KI on desktop. For **Tauri local-first** work, prefer `.cursor/rules/scriptony-desktop-dev.mdc` and `docs/DESKTOP_FIRST_DEV.md` — do not require Appwrite env or deploy unless the ticket says so.

**Frontend (Mac):** Projektroot `.env.local` aus `.env.local.example`: `VITE_APPWRITE_ENDPOINT`, `VITE_APPWRITE_PROJECT_ID`, sowie `VITE_APPWRITE_FUNCTIONS_BASE_URL` oder `VITE_BACKEND_API_BASE_URL` (Basis-URL der deployten `scriptony-*` Funktionen). Redirects/Web-URL auf **Port 3000** (`vite.config.ts`): `VITE_APP_WEB_URL`, `VITE_AUTH_REDIRECT_URL`, `VITE_PASSWORD_RESET_REDIRECT_URL`.

**Appwrite Console:** OAuth- und Web-Redirects müssen die gleichen Origins enthalten wie die Vite-App (lokal und Production).

**Testumgebung:** `npm run dev` + erreichbare Appwrite-Instanz + Functions-Basis-URL. Prüfen: `npm run verify:test-env` (liest `.env.local`). KI (`scriptony-assistant`): nach CLI-Login `npm run appwrite:setup:assistant`, Domains in der Console, optional `npm run appwrite:sync:function-domains`.

**Backend-Code:** `functions/` — gemeinsame GraphQL-kompatible Schicht unter `functions/_shared/` spricht mit Appwrite Databases/Storage (kein Hasura/Postgres im Browser).
